 419:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-app/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * @return uint16_t Received data over UART communication channel.
 420:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-app/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * \par<b>Description</b><br>
 421:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-app/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * Provides one word of data received over UART communication channel.\n\n
 422:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-app/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * Based on the channel configuration, data is either read from the receive FIFO or RBUF register.
 423:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-app/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * Before returning the value, there is no check for data validity. User should check the appropria
 424:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-app/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * data receive flags(standard receive/alternative receive/FIFO standard receive/FIFO alternative r
 425:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-app/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * before executing the API. Reading from an empty receive FIFO can generate a receive error event.
 426:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-app/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  *
 427:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-app/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * \par<b>Related APIs:</b><BR>
 428:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-app/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * XMC_UART_CH_GetStatusFlag(), XMC_UART_CH_Transmit() \n\n\n
